name: Aegean
description: Native to the Greek islands known as the Cyclades in the Aegean Sea, these are natural cats, meaning they developed without humans getting involved in their breeding. As a breed, Aegean Cats are rare, although they are numerous on their home islands. They are generally friendly toward people and can be excellent cats for families with children.

name: Abyssinian
description: The Abyssinian is one of the oldest known breeds. They are known for their playful and curious nature, often described as dog-like in their loyalty. They have a distinctive ticked coat and are very agile.

name: Balinese
description: The Balinese is a long-haired version of the Siamese. Known for their grace and elegance, Balinese cats are highly intelligent and love to be involved in their owners' activities.

name: Bengal
description: The Bengal cat is known for its striking leopard-like appearance and playful, energetic nature. They are very active and require plenty of stimulation.

name: Burmese
description: The Burmese cat is known for its sleek, shiny coat and affectionate personality. They are very people-oriented and enjoy being the center of attention.

name: Maine Coon
description: The Maine Coon is one of the largest domesticated cat breeds, known for its friendly and gentle nature. They have a long, thick coat and are often referred to as 'gentle giants.'
